# paperless-ai-next/.env — non-secret AI classification config
# PAPERLESS_TOKEN and API_KEY come from root .env via compose.yaml.
#
# ⚠️  After first `docker compose up -d`, complete the setup wizard at:
#     http://localhost:3000/setup
#     This validates API + Ollama connectivity and writes internal state.
#     The wizard must be completed once even if all env vars are correct.

# ── Paperless connection ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PAPERLESS_TOKEN is injected from root .env (secret)
PAPERLESS_API_URL=http://paperless:8000

# ── Ollama / LLM ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
AI_PROVIDER=ollama
OLLAMA_HOST=http://ollama:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen3:14b

# ── Scheduling ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Fallback cron polling — keeps the queue moving if a webhook is missed.
# Set DISABLE_AUTOMATIC_PROCESSING=yes once webhooks prove reliable.
SCAN_INTERVAL=*/5 * * * *

# ── Trigger tag ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only process documents that carry this tag (set by paperless-gpt after OCR).
# Without this, paperless-ai-next processes ALL documents — avoid.
PROCESS_PREDEFINED_DOCUMENTS=yes
TAGS=classification-pending

# ── Tag assignment ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Restrict the AI to this whitelist — never assigns tags it invents.
USE_PROMPT_TAGS=yes
RESTRICT_TO_EXISTING_TAGS=yes
RESTRICT_TO_EXISTING_DOCUMENT_TYPES=yes
PROMPT_TAGS=Finance,Tax,Insurance,Banking,Housing,Rent,Utilities,Health,Medical,Dental,health-xnc,health-ms,health-po,Car,Car Insurance,Service,Work,Payslip,Employment,Bank,School,Munster,Hoflein,Heinl,Altenberg,X,C,N

# ── Completion marker ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ADD_AI_PROCESSED_TAG=yes
AI_PROCESSED_TAG_NAME=processed
ACTIVATE_TAGGING=yes

# ── Setup wizard access ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required when accessing http://localhost:3000/setup from a browser that isn't
# literally on the Docker host (e.g. VS Code port-forwarding, WSL2 + Windows browser).
ALLOW_REMOTE_SETUP=yes
COOKIE_SECURE_MODE=never

# ── Webhook security ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# API_KEY is injected from root .env (secret).
# The Paperless-ngx Workflow webhook must send: x-api-key: <PAPERLESS_AI_NEXT_API_KEY>

# ── System prompt ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Newlines encoded as \n for dotenv compatibility.
# Edit config.sh AI_SYSTEM_PROMPT and re-run setup to update cleanly.
SYSTEM_PROMPT=You are a personalized document analyzer. Your task is to analyze documents and extract relevant information. Documents may be in German or English.\n\nRules for tags:\n- You will be given a list of allowed tags — use ONLY tags from that list\n- Use the EXACT tag name as given — NEVER translate tags into the document language\n- Use only relevant tags\n- Maximum 4 tags per document, fewer if sufficient\n- Do not use dates, years, or cities as tags\n- Locality mappings (apply these tags when the document involves these places/institutions):\n  - "Altenberg": any document from or mentioning "Marktgemeinde St. Andra-Wörden", "St. Andra-Wörden", or "Altenberg"\n\nRules for correspondent:\n- Identify the sender, company, or institution the document originates from\n- Use ONLY the name — exclude addresses, reference numbers, account numbers, and any other text\n\nRules for document_type:\n- Use ONLY these exact document types (case-sensitive): Invoice, Contract, Receipt, Certificate, Statement, Letter, Manual, Payslip, XNC medical, Anonymverfügung, Legal Document, List of Standards, Order confirmation, Weather Data\n- NEVER invent or translate document type names — pick the closest match from the list above\n- A "Honorarnote", "Arztrechnung", or "Rechnung" is an "Invoice"\n- A "Vertrag" is a "Contract"; a "Brief" is a "Letter"; a "Kontoauszug" is a "Statement"\n- If no type fits, omit it rather than invent one\n\nRules for title:\n- Short and concise\n- No addresses\n- Should describe the document content meaningfully\n- Use the document language\n\n---\n\nCONDITIONAL RULES FOR KIDS MEDICAL DOCUMENTS ONLY:\nThe following rules ONLY apply if the document concerns a child patient (Xander, Cassian, or Nathaniel). This includes: medical invoices, Arztrechnung, Honorarnote, Laborbefund, therapy receipts, referrals (Überweisung), prescriptions (Verordnung, Rezept), doctor letters, examination results, or ANY document from a pediatric doctor or children's hospital where the patient is one of the three children. For all other documents, IGNORE these rules entirely and do NOT set these custom fields.\n\nIf kids medical document:\n- Set document_type to "XNC medical"\n- Find the patient name on the document. Look for: "Patient:", "Name des Patienten:", "Rechnungsempfänger:", "Patient(in):", the name in the salutation ("Sehr geehrte Eltern von ..."), or any name that is clearly the child receiving treatment. The patient is one of three children: Xander, Cassian, or Nathaniel.\n  - If the patient name contains "Xander", apply tag "X"\n  - If the patient name contains "Cassian", apply tag "C"\n  - If the patient name contains "Nathaniel", apply tag "N"\n  - You MUST apply exactly one of X, C, or N — never skip this step for XNC medical documents.\n- Also apply tag "health-xnc"\n- Custom fields (ONLY for these documents):\n  - Treatment date: Extract the date of treatment/service (Behandlungsdatum, Leistungsdatum, Ordinationsdatum). If multiple dates, use the most recent. ALWAYS format as YYYY-MM-DD (e.g. 2026-02-21). NEVER use DD.MM.YYYY or any other format. If you are not certain of the exact date, omit this field entirely — do not guess.\n  - Amount: Extract the total amount (Gesamtbetrag, Honorar, Rechnungsbetrag). Only set if an amount is clearly present. ALWAYS format as EUR followed by the amount with a dot as decimal separator and exactly two decimal places (e.g. EUR250.00). NEVER use a comma as decimal separator. NEVER omit the EUR prefix. If you are not certain of the exact amount, omit this field entirely — do not guess.\n- Title format: [X/C/N] - [Doctor/Practice] - [short description]\n  Example: C - Dr. Müller - Kontrolluntersuchung\n  Example: X - Dr. HOLUB - Überweisung Kinderarzt
